## 3. Label Files (`.txt` inside `labels/`)

Each image has a paired `.txt` file with the **same filename** in the `labels/` folder.
Each line = one annotated object, in YOLO normalised format:

```
<class_id>  <x_center>  <y_center>  <width>  <height>
```

All values are **normalised to [0, 1]** relative to image width/height.

```
# frame_0001.txt — two structures annotated
0  0.423  0.318  0.162  0.094
1  0.651  0.512  0.231  0.083
```

**Interpretation:**
- Line 1: `alpha_helix` (class 0), centre at (42.3%, 31.8%), 16.2% wide, 9.4% tall
- Line 2: `beta_sheet` (class 1), centre at (65.1%, 51.2%), 23.1% wide, 8.3% tall

**Why normalised?**
Normalisation makes label files resolution-independent. If a frame is resized
from 1280×720 → 384×216 (same aspect ratio), the fractional coordinates
still correctly locate the helix or sheet — no re-annotation needed.

